d N-terminus, t-butyl ester protected C-terminus, with Phg-Ala sequence.\n\nFINAL_RESULT:\n  UUID: d677455f-772d-4c80-a382-aa671497e57b\n  PREDICTED_SMILES: CC(C)(C)OC(=O)NC(C1=CC=CC=C1)C(=O)NC(C)C(=O)OC(C)(C)C\n  CONFIDENCE: 0.95\n  REASON_BRIEF: The formula C20H30N2O5 and NMR data confirm a dipeptide derivative containing Phenylglycine and Alanine. The large alkyl integration (21H) confirms Boc and t-butyl ester groups plus an Ala methyl. The coupling of the amide doublet (6.34 ppm) to the Ala alpha-proton (4.46 ppm) establishes the sequence as Boc-Phg-Ala-OtBu.",
